Subject: [experiment] ESM4 raw actor keyframe composition

Status: experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Depends-on: 0011-esm4-actor-controller-basis-audit.patch,
0012-esm4-native-callback-basis-audit.patch,
0014-esm4-actor-root-attachment-audit.patch.
Source clue: D:\code\vulkanOpenMW\nikami-openmw-lab-publish commit
4d7450c412 "Fix FNV actor pose basis and sleeve skinning".

The FO3/FNV close-burst screenshots still show upside-down actors after root
wrapper probes and idle-freeze probes. Root attachment telemetry shows static
actor assembly starts coherent, then lower-body targets move above the pelvis
when animation is applied. Prior local history points at double application of
the Fallout actor basis: native keyframe callbacks already emit actor-local
samples, while the manual composer applies bind-relative rotation.

This patch removes the extra basis application from native callback sampling and
makes the manual Fallout composer request raw NifOsg key samples explicitly. It
keeps the basis audit active for Fallout actor-basis bones so proof ledgers can
confirm whether applied-vs-raw deltas collapse to zero.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp
